Email Header Analysis – Sample 4

Subject: Dropbox Storage Limit Reached
Sender: support@dropbox-verification.com

Findings:

Sender Domain:
dropbox-verification.com

Indicators:

• Domain impersonates the legitimate Dropbox service
• Sender domain does not match the official Dropbox domain (dropbox.com)
• Generic greeting ("Dear User")
• Urgent request to verify account
• Suspicious external verification link

Authentication Indicators (Expected):

SPF: Fail or Unknown
DKIM: Not present
DMARC: Fail

Conclusion:

The sender domain attempts to imitate Dropbox branding but does not belong to the official Dropbox infrastructure. The email uses urgency and account verification language to trick users into clicking a malicious link. This email is classified as a phishing attempt.
